The paper discusses methods to identify field-specific excellence in cities based on highly-cited papers published in information science. This falls under the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and sound (cs.SD). However, since the paper focuses on the analysis of publication and citation data, the first two sub-categories (cs.DL and cs.IR) are the most likely.
